Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Macro Hygiene Module

Provides comprehensive macro hygiene capabilities including:
- Variable scoping and capture prevention
- Hygienic macro expansion
- Scope isolation and management
- Variable renaming and conflict resolution
- Cross-module hygiene support
- Hygiene debugging and validation
- AI/agent-friendly hygiene tools
- Production-ready hygiene with error handling

Features:
- Advanced variable scoping with capture prevention
- Hygienic macro expansion with proper isolation
- Scope management with conflict resolution
- Variable renaming with uniqueness guarantees
- Cross-module hygiene with dependency tracking
- Comprehensive hygiene debugging and validation
- AI/agent-friendly hygiene development tools
- Production-ready hygiene with comprehensive error handling
:End Note

Note: Hygiene Types and Data Structures
Type called "HygieneContext":
    scope_stack as List[Scope]
    variable_registry as VariableRegistry
    renaming_map as Dictionary[String, String]
    conflict_resolver as ConflictResolver
    hygiene_validator as HygieneValidator
    debug_tracer as HygieneDebugTracer
    performance_monitor as HygienePerformanceMonitor
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "Scope":
    scope_id as String
    parent_scope as Optional[String]
    variables as Dictionary[String, VariableInfo]
    macro_definitions as List[String]
    hygiene_rules as List[HygieneRule]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "VariableRegistry":
    global_variables as Dictionary[String, VariableInfo]
    scope_variables as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, VariableInfo]]
    variable_history as List[VariableHistoryEntry]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ConflictResolver":
    resolvers as Dictionary[String, ConflictResolverFunction]
    strategies as Dictionary[String, ConflictResolutionStrategy]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "HygieneValidator":
    validators as Dictionary[String, HygieneValidatorFunction]
    rules as List[HygieneValidationRule]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "HygieneDebugTracer":
    trace_level as String
    trace_output as List[HygieneTraceEntry]
    hygiene_events as List[HygieneEvent]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "HygienePerformanceMonitor":
    metrics as Dictionary[String, HygienePerformanceMetric]
    thresholds as Dictionary[String, Float]
    alerts as List[HygienePerformanceAlert]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "VariableInfo":
    name as String
    original_name as String
    scope_id as String
    variable_type as String
    is_captured as Boolean
    capture_depth as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "VariableHistoryEntry":
    timestamp as Float
    action as String
    variable_name as String
    scope_id as String
    details as Dictionary[String, Any]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ConflictResolverFunction is Function that takes conflict as VariableConflict and context as HygieneContext returns String

Type called "ConflictResolutionStrategy":
    strategy_type as String
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type HygieneValidatorFunction is Function that takes hygiene_context as HygieneContext returns Boolean

Type called "HygieneValidationRule":
    rule_type as String
    condition as String
    action as String
    severity as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "HygieneTraceEntry":
    timestamp as Float
    level as String
    message as String
    scope_id as String
    variable_name as String
    action as String
    data as Dictionary[String, Any]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "HygieneEvent":
    event_type as String
    timestamp as Float
    scope_id as String
    variable_name as String
    details as Dictionary[String, Any]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "HygienePerformanceMetric":
    name as String
    value as Float
    unit as String
    timestamp as Float
    scope_id as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "HygienePerformanceAlert":
    metric as String
    threshold as Float
    current_value as Float
    severity as String
    timestamp as Float
    scope_id as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "VariableConflict":
    variable_name as String
    scope_id as String
    conflict_type as String
    conflicting_variables as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type HygieneResult is:
    | HygieneSuccess with scope_id as String and variables as Dictionary[String, VariableInfo] and performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    | HygieneError with error as String and details as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | HygieneWarning with warning as String and scope_id as String and variables as Dictionary[String, VariableInfo]

Note: Core Hygiene Functions
Process called "create_hygiene_context" that takes macro_context as MacroContext returns HygieneContext:
    Let scope_stack be list containing
    Let variable_registry be create_variable_registry
    Let renaming_map be dictionary containing
    Let conflict_resolver be create_conflict_resolver
    Let hygiene_validator be create_hygiene_validator
    Let debug_tracer be create_hygiene_debug_tracer
    Let performance_monitor be create_hygiene_performance_monitor
    
    Return HygieneContext with:
        scope_stack as scope_stack
        variable_registry as variable_registry
        renaming_map as renaming_map
        conflict_resolver as conflict_resolver
        hygiene_validator as hygiene_validator
        debug_tracer as debug_tracer
        performance_monitor as performance_monitor
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "enter_hygienic_scope" that takes context as HygieneContext and scope_id as String and parent_scope as Optional[String] returns HygieneResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    
    Try:
        Let new_scope be Scope with:
            scope_id as scope_id
            parent_scope as parent_scope
            variables as dictionary containing
            macro_definitions as list containing
            hygiene_rules as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add new_scope to context.scope_stack
        
        Let trace_entry be HygieneTraceEntry with:
            timestamp as start_time
            level as "info"
            message as "Entered hygienic scope: " plus scope_id
            scope_id as scope_id
            variable_name as ""
            action as "enter_scope"
            data as dictionary containing:
                "parent_scope" as parent_scope
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add trace_entry to context.debug_tracer.trace_output
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Let performance_metric be HygienePerformanceMetric with:
            name as "scope_creation_time"
            value as end_time minus start_time
            unit as "seconds"
            timestamp as end_time
            scope_id as scope_id
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Set context.performance_monitor.metrics["scope_creation_time"] to performance_metric
        
        Return HygieneSuccess with:
            scope_id as scope_id
            variables as new_scope.variables
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing:
                "scope_creation_time" as end_time minus start_time
        
    Catch error:
        Return HygieneError with error as error.message and details as dictionary containing

Process called "leave_hygienic_scope" that takes context as HygieneContext and scope_id as String returns HygieneResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    
    Try:
        Let scope_index be find_scope_index with context as context and scope_id as scope_id
        
        If scope_index is None:
            Return HygieneError with error as "Scope not found: " plus scope_id and details as dictionary containing
        
        Let scope be context.scope_stack[scope_index]
        Let variables be scope.variables
        
        Remove context.scope_stack[scope_index] from context.scope_stack
        
        Let trace_entry be HygieneTraceEntry with:
            timestamp as start_time
            level as "info"
            message as "Left hygienic scope: " plus scope_id
            scope_id as scope_id
            variable_name as ""
            action as "leave_scope"
            data as dictionary containing:
                "variable_count" as length of variables
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add trace_entry to context.debug_tracer.trace_output
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Let performance_metric be HygienePerformanceMetric with:
            name as "scope_cleanup_time"
            value as end_time minus start_time
            unit as "seconds"
            timestamp as end_time
            scope_id as scope_id
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Set context.performance_monitor.metrics["scope_cleanup_time"] to performance_metric
        
        Return HygieneSuccess with:
            scope_id as scope_id
            variables as variables
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing:
                "scope_cleanup_time" as end_time minus start_time
        
    Catch error:
        Return HygieneError with error as error.message and details as dictionary containing

Process called "register_variable_hygienically" that takes context as HygieneContext and variable_name as String and scope_id as String and variable_type as String returns HygieneResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    
    Try:
        Let scope be find_scope with context as context and scope_id as scope_id
        
        If scope is None:
            Return HygieneError with error as "Scope not found: " plus scope_id and details as dictionary containing
        
        Let conflict_check be check_variable_conflict with context as context and variable_name as variable_name and scope_id as scope_id
        
        If conflict_check is not None:
            Let resolved_name be resolve_variable_conflict with context as context and conflict as conflict_check
            
            If resolved_name is None:
                Return HygieneError with error as "Failed to resolve variable conflict" and details as dictionary containing
            
            Set variable_name to resolved_name
        
        Let variable_info be VariableInfo with:
            name as variable_name
            original_name as variable_name
            scope_id as scope_id
            variable_type as variable_type
            is_captured as false
            capture_depth as 0
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Set scope.variables[variable_name] to variable_info
        
        Let history_entry be VariableHistoryEntry with:
            timestamp as start_time
            action as "register"
            variable_name as variable_name
            scope_id as scope_id
            details as dictionary containing:
                "variable_type" as variable_type
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add history_entry to context.variable_registry.variable_history
        
        Let trace_entry be HygieneTraceEntry with:
            timestamp as start_time
            level as "info"
            message as "Registered variable hygienically: " plus variable_name
            scope_id as scope_id
            variable_name as variable_name
            action as "register_variable"
            data as dictionary containing:
                "variable_type" as variable_type
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add trace_entry to context.debug_tracer.trace_output
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Let performance_metric be HygienePerformanceMetric with:
            name as "variable_registration_time"
            value as end_time minus start_time
            unit as "seconds"
            timestamp as end_time
            scope_id as scope_id
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Set context.performance_monitor.metrics["variable_registration_time"] to performance_metric
        
        Return HygieneSuccess with:
            scope_id as scope_id
            variables as scope.variables
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing:
                "variable_registration_time" as end_time minus start_time
        
    Catch error:
        Return HygieneError with error as error.message and details as dictionary containing

Process called "resolve_variable_hygienically" that takes context as HygieneContext and variable_name as String and scope_id as String returns Optional[VariableInfo]:
    Try:
        Let scope be find_scope with context as context and scope_id as scope_id
        
        If scope is None:
            Return None
        
        If scope.variables contains variable_name:
            Return scope.variables[variable_name]
        
        Let parent_scope_id be scope.parent_scope
        While parent_scope_id is not None:
            Let parent_scope be find_scope with context as context and scope_id as parent_scope_id
            
            If parent_scope is None:
                Break
            
            If parent_scope.variables contains variable_name:
                Let variable_info be parent_scope.variables[variable_name]
                Set variable_info.is_captured to true
                Set variable_info.capture_depth to variable_info.capture_depth plus 1
                Return variable_info
            
            Set parent_scope_id to parent_scope.parent_scope
        
        Return None
        
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "apply_hygiene_rules" that takes context as HygieneContext and scope_id as String and rules as List[HygieneRule] returns HygieneResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    
    Try:
        Let scope be find_scope with context as context and scope_id as scope_id
        
        If scope is None:
            Return HygieneError with error as "Scope not found: " plus scope_id and details as dictionary containing
        
        For each rule in rules:
            Let rule_result be apply_hygiene_rule with context as context and scope as scope and rule as rule
            
            If rule_result is not None:
                Let trace_entry be HygieneTraceEntry with:
                    timestamp as get_current_time
                    level as "warning"
                    message as "Hygiene rule applied: " plus rule.rule_type
                    scope_id as scope_id
                    variable_name as rule.variable_pattern
                    action as "apply_rule"
                    data as dictionary containing:
                        "rule_type" as rule.rule_type
                        "action" as rule.action
                    metadata as dictionary containing
                
                Add trace_entry to context.debug_tracer.trace_output
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Let performance_metric be HygienePerformanceMetric with:
            name as "hygiene_rules_time"
            value as end_time minus start_time
            unit as "seconds"
            timestamp as end_time
            scope_id as scope_id
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Set context.performance_monitor.metrics["hygiene_rules_time"] to performance_metric
        
        Return HygieneSuccess with:
            scope_id as scope_id
            variables as scope.variables
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing:
                "hygiene_rules_time" as end_time minus start_time
        
    Catch error:
        Return HygieneError with error as error.message and details as dictionary containing

Process called "validate_hygiene" that takes context as HygieneContext returns Boolean:
    Try:
        For each validator_name in context.hygiene_validator.validators:
            Let validator_function be context.hygiene_validator.validators[validator_name]
            Let validation_result be validator_function with hygiene_context as context
            
            If not validation_result:
                Return false
        
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: Variable Registry Management
Process called "create_variable_registry" returns VariableRegistry:
    Return VariableRegistry with:
        global_variables as dictionary containing
        scope_variables as dictionary containing
        variable_history as list containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "find_scope" that takes context as HygieneContext and scope_id as String returns Optional[Scope]:
    For each scope in context.scope_stack:
        If scope.scope_id equals scope_id:
            Return scope
    
    Return None

Process called "find_scope_index" that takes context as HygieneContext and scope_id as String returns Optional[Integer]:
    For each index in range from 0 to length of context.scope_stack minus 1:
        Let scope be context.scope_stack[index]
        If scope.scope_id equals scope_id:
            Return index
    
    Return None

Process called "check_variable_conflict" that takes context as HygieneContext and variable_name as String and scope_id as String returns Optional[VariableConflict]:
    Try:
        Let scope be find_scope with context as context and scope_id as scope_id
        
        If scope is None:
            Return None
        
        Let conflicting_variables be list containing
        
        If scope.variables contains variable_name:
            Add variable_name to conflicting_variables
        
        Let parent_scope_id be scope.parent_scope
        While parent_scope_id is not None:
            Let parent_scope be find_scope with context as context and scope_id as parent_scope_id
            
            If parent_scope is None:
                Break
            
            If parent_scope.variables contains variable_name:
                Add variable_name to conflicting_variables
            
            Set parent_scope_id to parent_scope.parent_scope
        
        If length of conflicting_variables is greater than 0:
            Return VariableConflict with:
                variable_name as variable_name
                scope_id as scope_id
                conflict_type as "name_collision"
                conflicting_variables as conflicting_variables
                metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Return None
        
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "resolve_variable_conflict" that takes context as HygieneContext and conflict as VariableConflict returns Optional[String]:
    Try:
        Let resolver_function be context.conflict_resolver.resolvers[conflict.conflict_type] if context.conflict_resolver.resolvers contains conflict.conflict_type else default_conflict_resolver
        
        Let resolved_name be resolver_function with conflict as conflict and context as context
        
        If resolved_name is not None:
            Set context.renaming_map[conflict.variable_name] to resolved_name
        
        Return resolved_name
        
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "default_conflict_resolver" that takes conflict as VariableConflict and context as HygieneContext returns String:
    Let base_name be conflict.variable_name
    Let counter be 1
    
    While true:
        Let new_name be base_name plus "_" plus counter
        Let new_conflict be check_variable_conflict with context as context and variable_name as new_name and scope_id as conflict.scope_id
        
        If new_conflict is None:
            Return new_name
        
        Set counter to counter plus 1

Process called "apply_hygiene_rule" that takes context as HygieneContext and scope as Scope and rule as HygieneRule returns Optional[String]:
    Try:
        If rule.rule_type equals "rename":
            Let new_name be generate_unique_name with context as context and base_name as rule.variable_pattern and scope_id as scope.scope_id
            Return new_name
        
        If rule.rule_type equals "isolate":
            Let isolation_result be isolate_variable with context as context and variable_name as rule.variable_pattern and scope as scope
            Return isolation_result
        
        If rule.rule_type equals "capture":
            Let capture_result be capture_variable with context as context and variable_name as rule.variable_pattern and scope as scope
            Return capture_result
        
        Return None
        
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "generate_unique_name" that takes context as HygieneContext and base_name as String and scope_id as String returns String:
    Let counter be 1
    Let new_name be base_name
    
    While true:
        Let conflict be check_variable_conflict with context as context and variable_name as new_name and scope_id as scope_id
        
        If conflict is None:
            Return new_name
        
        Set new_name to base_name plus "_" plus counter
        Set counter to counter plus 1

Process called "isolate_variable" that takes context as HygieneContext and variable_name as String and scope as Scope returns String:
    Try:
        Let isolated_name be variable_name plus "_isolated_" plus scope.scope_id
        
        Let variable_info be VariableInfo with:
            name as isolated_name
            original_name as variable_name
            scope_id as scope.scope_id
            variable_type as "isolated"
            is_captured as false
            capture_depth as 0
            metadata as dictionary containing:
                "isolation_strategy" as "scope_based"
                "original_scope" as scope.scope_id
        
        Set scope.variables[isolated_name] to variable_info
        
        Let history_entry be VariableHistoryEntry with:
            timestamp as get_current_time
            action as "isolate"
            variable_name as isolated_name
            scope_id as scope.scope_id
            details as dictionary containing:
                "original_name" as variable_name
                "isolation_method" as "scope_based"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add history_entry to context.variable_registry.variable_history
        
        Return isolated_name
        
    Catch error:
        Return variable_name plus "_isolated_error"

Process called "capture_variable" that takes context as HygieneContext and variable_name as String and scope as Scope returns String:
    Try:
        Let parent_scope_id be scope.parent_scope
        If parent_scope_id is None:
            Return variable_name
        
        Let parent_scope be find_scope with context as context and scope_id as parent_scope_id
        If parent_scope is None:
            Return variable_name
        
        If not parent_scope.variables contains variable_name:
            Return variable_name
        
        Let parent_variable be parent_scope.variables[variable_name]
        Let captured_name be variable_name plus "_captured_" plus scope.scope_id
        
        Let captured_variable be VariableInfo with:
            name as captured_name
            original_name as parent_variable.original_name
            scope_id as scope.scope_id
            variable_type as "captured"
            is_captured as true
            capture_depth as parent_variable.capture_depth plus 1
            metadata as dictionary containing:
                "capture_strategy" as "parent_scope"
                "source_scope" as parent_scope_id
                "original_variable" as variable_name
        
        Set scope.variables[captured_name] to captured_variable
        
        Let history_entry be VariableHistoryEntry with:
            timestamp as get_current_time
            action as "capture"
            variable_name as captured_name
            scope_id as scope.scope_id
            details as dictionary containing:
                "original_name" as variable_name
                "source_scope" as parent_scope_id
                "capture_depth" as captured_variable.capture_depth
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add history_entry to context.variable_registry.variable_history
        
        Return captured_name
        
    Catch error:
        Return variable_name plus "_capture_error"

Note: Conflict Resolution Functions
Process called "create_conflict_resolver" returns ConflictResolver:
    Let resolvers be dictionary containing:
        "name_collision" as name_collision_resolver
        "scope_conflict" as scope_conflict_resolver
        "capture_conflict" as capture_conflict_resolver
    
    Let strategies be dictionary containing:
        "rename" as ConflictResolutionStrategy with:
            strategy_type as "rename"
            parameters as dictionary containing:
                "prefix" as "hygienic_"
                "suffix" as "_renamed"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        "isolate" as ConflictResolutionStrategy with:
            strategy_type as "isolate"
            parameters as dictionary containing:
                "scope_level" as "current"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        "capture" as ConflictResolutionStrategy with:
            strategy_type as "capture"
            parameters as dictionary containing:
                "capture_depth" as 1
            metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Return ConflictResolver with:
        resolvers as resolvers
        strategies as strategies
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "name_collision_resolver" that takes conflict as VariableConflict and context as HygieneContext returns String:
    Let strategy be context.conflict_resolver.strategies["rename"]
    Let prefix be strategy.parameters["prefix"]
    Let suffix be strategy.parameters["suffix"]
    
    Return prefix plus conflict.variable_name plus suffix

Process called "scope_conflict_resolver" that takes conflict as VariableConflict and context as HygieneContext returns String:
    Let strategy be context.conflict_resolver.strategies["isolate"]
    Let scope_level be strategy.parameters["scope_level"]
    
    If scope_level equals "current":
        Return conflict.variable_name plus "_isolated"
    Otherwise:
        Return conflict.variable_name plus "_scoped"

Process called "capture_conflict_resolver" that takes conflict as VariableConflict and context as HygieneContext returns String:
    Let strategy be context.conflict_resolver.strategies["capture"]
    Let capture_depth be strategy.parameters["capture_depth"]
    
    Return conflict.variable_name plus "_captured_" plus capture_depth

Note: Hygiene Validation Functions
Process called "create_hygiene_validator" returns HygieneValidator:
    Let validators be dictionary containing:
        "scope_integrity" as scope_integrity_validator
        "variable_uniqueness" as variable_uniqueness_validator
        "capture_safety" as capture_safety_validator
        "rule_compliance" as rule_compliance_validator
    
    Let rules be list containing:
        HygieneValidationRule with:
            rule_type as "scope_integrity"
            condition as "all_scopes_have_valid_parents"
            action as "report_error"
            severity as "error"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        HygieneValidationRule with:
            rule_type as "variable_uniqueness"
            condition as "no_duplicate_variables_in_scope"
            action as "report_warning"
            severity as "warning"
            metadata as dictionary containing
        HygieneValidationRule with:
            rule_type as "capture_safety"
            condition as "captured_variables_are_safe"
            action as "report_info"
            severity as "info"
            metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Return HygieneValidator with:
        validators as validators
        rules as rules
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "scope_integrity_validator" that takes hygiene_context as HygieneContext returns Boolean:
    Try:
        For each scope in hygiene_context.scope_stack:
            If scope.parent_scope is not None:
                Let parent_exists be false
                For each parent_scope in hygiene_context.scope_stack:
                    If parent_scope.scope_id equals scope.parent_scope:
                        Set parent_exists to true
                        Break
                
                If not parent_exists:
                    Return false
        
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "variable_uniqueness_validator" that takes hygiene_context as HygieneContext returns Boolean:
    Try:
        For each scope in hygiene_context.scope_stack:
            Let variable_names be list containing
            For each variable_name in scope.variables:
                Add variable_name to variable_names
            
            Let unique_names be remove_duplicates with list as variable_names
            If length of variable_names is not equal to length of unique_names:
                Return false
        
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "capture_safety_validator" that takes hygiene_context as HygieneContext returns Boolean:
    Try:
        For each scope in hygiene_context.scope_stack:
            For each variable_name in scope.variables:
                Let variable_info be scope.variables[variable_name]
                If variable_info.is_captured and variable_info.capture_depth is greater than 10:
                    Return false
        
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "rule_compliance_validator" that takes hygiene_context as HygieneContext returns Boolean:
    Try:
        For each scope in hygiene_context.scope_stack:
            For each rule in scope.hygiene_rules:
                Let compliance_result be check_rule_compliance with rule as rule and scope as scope
                If not compliance_result:
                    Return false
        
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "check_rule_compliance" that takes rule as HygieneRule and scope as Scope returns Boolean:
    Try:
        If rule.rule_type equals "rename":
            For each variable_name in scope.variables:
                Let variable_info be scope.variables[variable_name]
                If matches with text as variable_info.original_name and pattern as rule.variable_pattern:
                    If variable_info.name equals variable_info.original_name:
                        Return false
            Return true
        
        Otherwise if rule.rule_type equals "isolate":
            For each variable_name in scope.variables:
                Let variable_info be scope.variables[variable_name]
                If matches with text as variable_info.original_name and pattern as rule.variable_pattern:
                    If variable_info.variable_type is not equal to "isolated":
                        Return false
            Return true
        
        Otherwise if rule.rule_type equals "capture":
            For each variable_name in scope.variables:
                Let variable_info be scope.variables[variable_name]
                If matches with text as variable_info.original_name and pattern as rule.variable_pattern:
                    If not variable_info.is_captured:
                        Return false
            Return true
        
        Otherwise if rule.rule_type equals "no_capture":
            For each variable_name in scope.variables:
                Let variable_info be scope.variables[variable_name]
                If matches with text as variable_info.original_name and pattern as rule.variable_pattern:
                    If variable_info.is_captured:
                        Return false
            Return true
        
        Otherwise if rule.rule_type equals "unique_names":
            Let used_names be list containing
            For each variable_name in scope.variables:
                If used_names contains variable_name:
                    Return false
                Add variable_name to used_names
            Return true
        
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "remove_duplicates" that takes list as List[String] returns List[String]:
    Let unique_list be list containing
    For each item in list:
        If not unique_list contains item:
            Add item to unique_list
    Return unique_list

Note: Debug and Performance Monitoring Functions
Process called "create_hygiene_debug_tracer" returns HygieneDebugTracer:
    Return HygieneDebugTracer with:
        trace_level as "info"
        trace_output as list containing
        hygiene_events as list containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_hygiene_performance_monitor" returns HygienePerformanceMonitor:
    Return HygienePerformanceMonitor with:
        metrics as dictionary containing
        thresholds as dictionary containing:
            "scope_creation_time" as 0.1
            "variable_registration_time" as 0.01
            "hygiene_rules_time" as 0.05
        alerts as list containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "add_hygiene_event" that takes context as HygieneContext and event_type as String and scope_id as String and variable_name as String and details as Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let event be HygieneEvent with:
            event_type as event_type
            timestamp as get_current_time
            scope_id as scope_id
            variable_name as variable_name
            details as details
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Add event to context.debug_tracer.hygiene_events
        
    Catch error:
        Note: Ignore error in event logging

Process called "get_hygiene_trace" that takes context as HygieneContext returns List[HygieneTraceEntry]:
    Return context.debug_tracer.trace_output

Process called "get_hygiene_events" that takes context as HygieneContext returns List[HygieneEvent]:
    Return context.debug_tracer.hygiene_events

Process called "clear_hygiene_trace" that takes context as HygieneContext:
    Set context.debug_tracer.trace_output to list containing
    Set context.debug_tracer.hygiene_events to list containing

Process called "get_hygiene_performance_metrics" that takes context as HygieneContext returns Dictionary[String, HygienePerformanceMetric]:
    Return context.performance_monitor.metrics

Process called "get_hygiene_performance_alerts" that takes context as HygieneContext returns List[HygienePerformanceAlert]:
    Return context.performance_monitor.alerts

Process called "set_hygiene_performance_threshold" that takes context as HygieneContext and metric as String and threshold as Float returns Boolean:
    Try:
        Set context.performance_monitor.thresholds[metric] to threshold
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: Pattern Matching Utility Functions
Process called "matches" that takes text as String and pattern as String returns Boolean:
    Import "re"
    Try:
        If pattern equals "*":
            Return true
        
        If pattern contains "*":
            Let regex_pattern be pattern.replace with old as "*" and new as ".*"
            Return re.match with pattern as regex_pattern and string as text is not None
        
        Return text equals pattern
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Import "time"
    Try:
        Return time.time
    Catch error:
        Return 0.0 